\subsection ZORBA_VERIFY_PEER_SSL_CERTIFICATE ZORBA_VERIFY_PEER_SSL_CERTIFICATE
Default OFF
External dependency: curl with ssl and CA certifs file

In order to use a more reliable SSL connection for data transfer, CURL library can verify
the certificate of the peer against the list of CA certificates in the local dir.
If you intend to use this option you have to provide CURL this CA certifs file.
By default Zorba will download https files without checking the SSL certificate.

\subsection ZORBA_WITH_FILE_ACCESS ZORBA_WITH_FILE_ACCESS
Default ON
External dependency: none

You can use this option to restrict Zorba to not be able to use fn:doc on local files.

