\subsection ZORBA_WITH_REST ZORBA_WITH_REST
Default ON
External dependency: curl

This option activates the access to the internet through CURL library, either downloading documents from http:// or accessing webservices through REST.

\subsection ZORBA_WITH_SSL ZORBA_WITH_SSL
Default ON
External dependency: curl with ssl

If you don't have or don't use CURL library with SSL built in, then you can use this option to disable SSL access.

\subsection ZORBA_WITH_TIDY ZORBA_WITH_TIDY
Default ON
External dependency: libtidy

Lib tidy is used to transform html docs into xml docs before loading into Zorba store.
If you don't need this feature or cannot set up tidy library, then you can disable this feature.

\subsection ZORBA_XQUERYX ZORBA_XQUERYX
Default OFF
External dependency: libxml2, libxslt

You can activate XQueryX support by this option. After that you can compile and run XQueryX code through the normal api,
and Zorba is able to detect the difference between XQueryX and XQuery code and compile accordingly.
After enabling this option, the XQuery code can still be used.
XQueryX and XQueryX Update are supported.


